{id:"api-2014-spells-entangle",name:"Entangle",content:[{id:"Title",content:"Entangle"},{id:"StatGrid",content:[{title:"Level",content:"1"},{title:"Casting Time",content:"1 action"},{title:"Range",content:"90 feet (20ft cube)"},{title:"Components",content:"V, S"},{title:"Duration",content:"Up to 1 minute"},{title:"School",content:"Conjuration"},{title:"Save",content:"STR Save"}]},{id:"Subtitle",content:"Effect"},{id:"MultiText",content:["Grasping weeds and vines sprout from the ground in a 20-foot square starting form a point within range. For the duration, these plants turn the ground in the area into difficult terrain.","A creature in the area when you cast the spell must succeed on a strength saving throw or be restrained by the entangling plants until the spell ends. A creature restrained by the plants can use its action to make a Strength check against your spell save DC. On a success, it frees itself.","When the spell ends, the conjured plants wilt away."]}]}